;The Internet is becoming an increasingly important part of our lives.
Ri K'amaya'l jutaqil yalan rejqalem pa qak'aslem.


;The Mozilla project is a global community of people who believe that openness, innovation, and opportunity are key to the continued health of the Internet. We have worked together since 1998 to ensure that the Internet is developed in a way that benefits everyone. We are best known for creating the Mozilla Firefox web browser.
Ri Mozilla Nimasamaj jun aj ruwach'ulew kitinamit winaqi', ri nikinimaj chi ri tikirib'äl, tz'ukuj chuqa' ri samaj yalan kejqalem chi re ri raxnaqil K'amaya'l. Pa 1998 ojsamajinäq pe junam richin nijikib'äx chi ri K'amaya'l tinuk' richin rutzil ri winaqilem. Yalan etaman qawäch ruma xqanük' ri Mozilla Firefox ajk'amaya'l Okik'amaya'l.


;The Mozilla project uses a community-based approach to create world-class open source software and to develop new types of collaborative activities. We create communities of people involved in making the Internet experience better for all of us.
Ri Mozilla nimasamaj nisamäj achi'el pa jun tinamït, akuchi' nunük' rukema' jaqäl b'itz'ib' yalan e ütz chuqa' yerunük' k'ak'a' to'onel taq samaj. Yeqanük' tinamït winaqi' akuchi' niqaq'i' qonojel jun utziläj etamab'äl pa K'amaya'l.


;As a result of these efforts, we have distilled a set of principles that we believe are critical for the Internet to continue to benefit the public good as well as commercial aspects of life. We set out these principles below.
Ri q'i'on rik'in re taq uchuq'a' re', eqanuk'un jujun ruk'u'x taq tzij, ri niqana'ojij chi e k'atzinel richin chi ri K'amaya'l tajin keruto' achi'el ri ajwinäq wachinäq chuqa' ri k'ayin wachinäq pa k'aslemal. Ja re yeqacholajij qa re ruk'u'x taq tzij re'.


;The goals for the Manifesto are to:
Ri taq rurayb'al Tzijoxïk ja re':


;articulate a vision for the Internet that Mozilla participants want the Mozilla Foundation to pursue;
tiya' retal jun rutzub'al K'amaya'l, akuchi' ri yeto'on pa Mozilla niqajo' chi troqaj ri Mozilla Moloj;


;speak to people whether or not they have a technical background;
yojtikïr yojtzijon kik'in ri winaqi', k'o o manäq etamel taq kina'oj;


;make Mozilla contributors proud of what we're doing and motivate us to continue; and
tiq'ï' chi ri e ruto'onela' Mozilla tikina' ki' chi rij ri tajin niqab'än richin chi tuyäk qak'u'x richin k'a yojsamäj; chuqa'


;provide a framework for other people to advance this vision of the Internet.
tiya' jun tikirib'äl richin chi ri ch'aqa' chik winaqi' tikutzilaj re rutzub'al K'amaya'l re'.


;These principles will not come to life on their own. People are needed to make the Internet open and participatory - people acting as individuals, working together in groups, and leading others. The Mozilla Foundation is committed to advancing the principles set out in the Mozilla Manifesto. We invite others to join us and make the Internet an ever better place for everyone.
Re taq ruk'u'x tzi re' man pa kiyonil ta xkeb'anatäj. Ye'ajowäx winaqi' richin nib'an chi ri K'amaya'l tok jun jaqäl chuqa' to'onel k'ojlib'äl, winaqi' ri yesamäj kiyonil chuqa' pa molaj chuqa' winaqi' ri ye'ok kik'amöl b'ey ch'aqa' chik. Ri Mozilla Moloj nuya' rutzij chi nib'iyin kik'in ri ruk'u'x taq tzij ya'on ketal pa re rutzijoxik re'. Yeqapeyoj ch'aqa' chik chi ke'ok pa re nimasamaj re', richin ke ri' niqab'än chi re ri K'amaya'l jun utziläj k'ojlib'äl qichin qonojel.


